# ── Cloudflare Pages redirect rules for frontierprotocol.app ─────────────────
#
# /nft/metadata/* is served by the Express backend (server/routes.ts), not by
# the static Vite build. Plot NFT ASAs carry a URL of the form
#   https://frontierprotocol.app/nft/metadata/<plotId>#arc3
# (see server/services/chain/land.ts:54), so wallets and indexers resolve the
# branded-domain URL — which currently falls through to the SPA shell because
# nothing in client/public/ claims the path. Proxy the path to the Fly backend
# so wallets get a real ARC-3 JSON body.
#
# The static Vite build still owns:
#   /nft/biomes/*        → static PNG/SVG biome art (client/public/nft/biomes/)
#   /assets/*, /images/*, /textures/*, /story/*, /favicon.png, /robots.txt,
#     /sitemap.xml, /globe-rebuild-preview.html
#   and every SPA route (/*) → index.html (the SPA fallback below)
#
# ORDER MATTERS in Cloudflare Pages: each request matches the FIRST rule whose
# source pattern matches. The /nft/metadata/* proxy is therefore listed
# BEFORE the /* SPA fallback so the catch-all never shadows it.
#
# Non-goals:
#   - does not change NFT URL construction in server/services/chain/* (URLs
#     stay on frontierprotocol.app — that's what minted ASAs already point at).
#   - does not change the Express route or the server build.
#   - does not touch /api/* (the client bundles VITE_API_URL to Fly directly).
#   - does not touch /nft/biomes/* (static assets remain on the CDN).

# Proxy plot/commander/weapon NFT metadata to the Fly backend (no redirect — the
# wallet sees the branded-domain URL but the body is the backend's JSON).
# Cloudflare Pages's static-asset serving wins for paths that exist on the CDN,
# so /nft/biomes/* is unaffected.
/nft/metadata/commander/:commanderId  https://frontiernext.fly.dev/nft/metadata/commander/:commanderId  200
/nft/metadata/weapon/:weaponId       https://frontiernext.fly.dev/nft/metadata/weapon/:weaponId       200
/nft/metadata/:plotId                 https://frontiernext.fly.dev/nft/metadata/:plotId                 200

# SPA fallback — deep client routes (wouter) get the index.html shell.
/*                                  /index.html                                                         200
